title: China Officials Soften Tone on Covid Curbs Amid Protests
description: Health officials cited the less deadly Omicron variant in urging lighter lockdowns, but whether Beijing is shifting policy is unknown.

title: OPEC+ Favors Maintaining Flat Production, Delegates Say
description: The 13-member group and other big oil producers are likely to decide to keep output levels flat at their meeting Sunday, the group’s delegates said.

title: Israel Moves Troubled Military Unit Out of West Bank
description: The Israel Defense Forces is removing the Netzah Yehuda from the West Bank amid recent allegations of abuse and disciplinary action against soldiers accused of mistreating Palestinians.

title: China's Latest Rocket Sends New Crew to Finish Tiangong Space Station
description: The crew of the Shenzhou-15 spacecraft will conduct scientific experiments and complete the station, marking a feat of China’s space program.

title: Nuclear Stockpile Makes China a Growing Rival, Pentagon Says
description: Beijing is on pace to challenge any attempt from Washington to intervene in a potential crisis with Taiwan, according to the annual assessment.

title: Iraq and Iran Agree to Tighten Border Security Amid Unrest
description: Tehran accuses Kurdish groups based in northern Iraq of being involved in a monthslong antigovernment protest movement inside Iran.

title: Behind Chinese Covid Protests, Economic Worries Simmer Among Youth
description: China’s weekend protests, while mainly about Covid controls, also reflected young people’s anxiety over job prospects, raising stakes for Beijing to reignite growth.

title: Global Poor Lose Services as Developing Countries Face Higher Debt Payments
description: A record buildup in developing-world debt is leading to blackouts and healthcare cuts, threatening a lost decade of growth.

title: NATO Chief Urges Military Support for Ukraine as Russian Attacks Rage On
description: Jens Stoltenberg said the alliance must deny Moscow a victory that would embolden Russian President Vladimir Putin and other authoritarian leaders.

title: Russia's War in Ukraine Shifts Black Sea From NATO's Edge to Center Stage
description: The Black Sea security will permeate the agenda when NATO foreign ministers meet in Romania’s capital.

title: Inside Ukraine's Blackouts: Fraught Operations, Candlelit Concerts, Anger With Russia
description: Russia has stepped up its missile volleys in a bid to deprive Ukrainians of comfort and weaken support for the defense effort.

title: China Covid Protesters Become Targets of Beijing's Surveillance State
description: Chinese police have begun leveraging the powers of the country’s surveillance state to go after demonstrators who participated in rare public displays of defiance over the government’s stringent Covid control policies.

title: Ukraine War's Economic Ripples Sow Discord Between Washington, Allies
description: French President Macron’s visit to the U.S. is likely to focus on trade and geopolitical concerns, as European officials begin to express frustration at their increasing reliance on the U.S. for security and economic stability as the war in Ukraine continues.
